description:
&lt;p&gt;Mary Seacole Ward 2 is a 14 bedded female acute inpatient unit. It supports women within Birmingham with mental illness. Service users often have complex physical health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve working closely with a clinical team within the hospital, in order to gain a understanding of the clients and promote the concept of recovery, enhance the service users potential and recognise their well-being needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will have the ability to contribute to and follow a prescribed plan of care in relation to and individual’s presenting need including their physical health, discharge pathway and contributing to MDT discussions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will be highly motivated, with demonstrable experience in mental health care. In return we offer highly supportive and cohesive multi-disciplinary teams with a range of senior professionals to ensure you are well supported and integrated into your role. You will be required to work across a 24/7 shift pattern.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have completed the University-affiliated program of preparation and have a professional identification number with the NMC.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAngela EatlyJob titleWard ManagerTelephone number0121 301 6127&lt;/p&gt;
